On April 13, 2018, the President signed two laws. The first law, H.R. 4547, called the "Strengthening Protections for Social Security Beneficiaries Act of 2018," makes changes to the representative payee system for Social Security beneficiaries. The second law, S. 772, called the "Ashlynne Mike AMBER Alert in Indian Country Act," renews and modifies the program that grants funds for AMBER Alert communication plans.